HEADWORD: Firman
<hw>Fir"man</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Firmans</plw> <pr>(#)</pr> <xex>or</xex> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[Pers. <ets>ferm⟦amac⟧n</ets>.]</ety> <def>In Turkey and some other
Oriental countries, a decree or mandate issued by the sovereign; a royal
order or grant; -- generally given for special objects, as to a traveler
to insure him protection and assistance.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>firmaun</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

